<article>Racer bicycles, also known as road bikes, are specifically designed for speed and efficiency on paved roads. Characterized by their lightweight frames, narrow tires, and drop handlebars, racer bikes prioritize aerodynamics and agility. They typically feature multiple gears, allowing riders to adjust resistance for various terrains. With a focus on performance, racer bicycles are favored by cyclists for road racing, endurance rides, and recreational cycling. Their sleek design and responsive handling make them ideal for covering long distances quickly. Racer bikes continue to evolve with advancements in materials and technology, offering cyclists an exhilarating ride experience with every pedal stroke.</article>
